name: indole-3-glycerol-phosphate synthase
comment: In some organisms, this enzyme is part of a multifunctional protein, together with one or more other components of the system for the biosynthesis of tryptophan [EC 2.4.2.18 (anthranilate phosphoribosyltransferase), EC 4.1.3.27 (anthranilate synthase), EC 4.2.1.20 (tryptophan synthase) and EC 5.3.1.24 (phosphoribosylanthranilate isomerase)].

orthologs.K13501: anthranilate synthase / indole-3-glycerol phosphate synthase / phosphoribosylanthranilate isomerase
